
[1]indemnification

   INDEMNIFICA'TION, n. [from indemnify.]

   1. The act of indemnifying, saving harmless, or securing against loss,
   damage or penalty.

   2. Security against loss.

   3. Reimbursement of loss, damage or penalty.
